<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 03 at 4:02PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
central Roanoke, northwestern Bedford and southern Botetourt
Counties, the City of Salem and the City of Roanoke through 430 PM
EDT...
At 402 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Blue Ridge, or near Montvale, moving southwest at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Troutville...
Stewartsville...
Montvale...
and Hollins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
